{"author":{"id":"1260ec7e1e5fa2a41651bb0f92ca6302285a1546d07f404ff26b865b47ab5c24"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1642530297,"nonce":"uTeA64yH0BdcVq9JF0Xe90efV/8=","metadata":{"github-id":"IC_kwDODBZtRc48ijf0","github-url":"https://github.com/dandi/dandi-cli/issues/867#issuecomment-1015691252"},"message":"\u003e @yarikoptic Why not request authentication iff the Dandiset's data indicates it's embargoed instead of relying on response codes?\n\nI feel that relying on \"standard\" response codes would make it more robust.  E.g. would we need to adjust code if later we introduce some \"restricted\" dandisets?  Also it allows for per-asset control of needing authentication or not: e.g. if some assets of interest in embargoed dandiset are \"public\" (I believe current implementation allows for that and such assets could be downloaded without authentication) -- why should we require authentication?","files":null}]}